backend.src.configurations package

Submodules

backend.src.configurations.base_config module

class backend.src.configurations.base_config.BaseConfig[source]

Bases: object

This class represents the base configuration for the project.

Configuration settings are defined as class variables. The settings include secret keys, SQLAlchemy settings, and JWT token settings.

Variables:

  • SECRET_KEY – A secret key for the application.

  • SQLALCHEMY_TRACK_MODIFICATIONS – A setting that determines if SQLAlchemy should track modifications.

  • JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRES – The duration before a JWT access token expires.

  • JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRES – The duration before a JWT refresh token expires.

  • JWT_SECRET_KEY – A secret key for JWT.

  • JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_LOCATION – The locations where the JWT access token can be found.

  • JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_LOCATION – The locations where the JWT refresh token can be found.

  • JWT_REFRESH_COOKIE_NAME – The name of the cookie that stores the JWT refresh token.

  • JWT_COOKIE_CSRF_PROTECT – A setting that determines if CSRF protection should be enabled for the JWT cookie.

JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRES = datetime.timedelta(seconds=1800)
JWT_ACCESS_TOKEN_LOCATION = ['headers']
JWT_COOKIE_CSRF_PROTECT = False
JWT_REFRESH_COOKIE_NAME = 'refresh_token'
JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_EXPIRES = datetime.timedelta(days=1)
JWT_REFRESH_TOKEN_LOCATION = ['cookies']
JWT_SECRET_KEY = '81718cf43282cf50174bbe80'
SECRET_KEY = '049fe579ccadcd74b9a66866'
SQLALCHEMY_TRACK_MODIFICATIONS = False

backend.src.configurations.dev_config module

class backend.src.configurations.dev_config.DevConfig[source]

Bases: BaseConfig

This class represents the development configuration for the project, which inherits from the base configuration.

It defines configuration settings specific to a development environment, including the database URI, SQLALCHEMY_ECHO and DEBUG settings.

Variables:

  • SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI – The URI for the development database.

  • SQLALCHEMY_ECHO – A setting that determines if SQLAlchemy should log SQL queries to the console.

  • DEBUG – A setting that determines if the application should run in debug mode.

DEBUG = True
SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI = 'sqlite:////home/levchmak/SWI/ski-share/backend/src/databases/dev.db'
SQLALCHEMY_ECHO = True

backend.src.configurations.prod_config module

class backend.src.configurations.prod_config.ProdConfig[source]

Bases: BaseConfig

This class represents the production configuration for the project, which inherits from the base configuration.

It defines configuration settings specific to a production environment, including the database URI, DEBUG, SQLALCHEMY_ECHO and SQLALCHEMY_TRACK_MODIFICATIONS settings.

Variables:

  • SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI – The URI for the production database.

  • DEBUG – A setting that determines if the application should run in debug mode.

  • SQLALCHEMY_ECHO – A setting that determines if SQLAlchemy should log SQL queries to the console.

  • SQLALCHEMY_TRACK_MODIFICATIONS – A setting that determines if SQLAlchemy should track modifications to objects and emit signals.

DEBUG = False
SQLALCHEMY_DATABASE_URI = 'sqlite:///prod.db'
SQLALCHEMY_ECHO = False
SQLALCHEMY_TRACK_MODIFICATIONS = False
